[
  {
    "id": "flow28",
    "type": "tab",
    "label": "MAVLink AI - 28 Sub Lights & Gripper",
    "disabled": false,
    "info": "Payload control is not drone-only. On an ArduSub ROV the payload verbs are the mission: lights are servo/RC channels and the manipulator is a gripper. This flow drives both with the mavlink-ai-payload node.\n\n1) Lights full (servo instance 9 \u2192 1900 \u00b5s), 2) lights dim (\u2192 1500 \u00b5s), 3) lights off (\u2192 1100 \u00b5s), 4) gripper grab, 5) gripper release. Servo instances/PWM values are vehicle-specific \u2014 check your SERVOn_FUNCTION assignment. Debug-wired only; add a connection to the payload nodes (or a mavlink-ai-out node) to actuate."
  },
